Worcester.W.H. Goulding House: The W.H. Goulding House is an historic house at 4 Dix Street in Worcester, Massachusetts. The ​2 1⁄2-story frame house was built between 1847 and 1849, and was originally located at 26 Harvard Street. The owner was Henry Goulding, owner of some of Worcester's largest industrial businesses and founder of the Worcester Mechanics' Association.
